Package org.eclipse.collections.impl.map.mutable

This package contains implementations of the MutableMap interface.

A MutableMap is an implementation of a Map which provides internal iterator methods matching the Smalltalk Collection protocol.

This package contains the following implementations:

  • MapAdapter - a MutableMap wrapper around a Map interface instance.
  • UnifiedMap - a map which uses a hashtable as its underlying data store and stores key/value pairs in consecutive locations in a single array.
  • SynchronizedMutableMap - a synchronized view of a map.
  • UnmodifiableMutableMap - an unmodifiable view of a map.

This package contains one factory implementation:

  • MutableMapFactoryImpl - a factory which creates instances of type MutableMap.
